history.content:
If you're swapping another class, then you could get stuck on the waitlist for 170. In other words, the situation is the same as being enrolled in a class and being waitlisted for another with a time conflict. When it is time for you to get into the class, the system would not be able to enroll you due to the time conflict and someone would need to manually enroll you (which is kind of a deadlock situation, as for someone to manually enroll you, there needs to space in the class and there would not be any because the system would skip you and automatically enroll the next person on the waitlist who does not have a conflict).

tldr; don't waitlist a time conflicted class.

Regarding your second question, there is no answer. I'd say your chances depend on whether the class is expanded or not.

By swapping the class instead of simply being on the waitlist, you are keeping your "options open".
